info.author: Taito Horiuchi
info.description:
Introduction
============

How to Use
----------
* Install the package from portal_quickinstaller.
* Content type called "Verkkomaksut Payment Adapter" can be added from FormFolder of PloneFormGen.
    * Remember, you need to add fixed point field or selection field with required box checked first, so that payment adapter knows which field to use as price charge field.



Changelog
=========
0.11.0 (2011-04-03)
-------------------
- Viewlet Manager added.
- Tested with Plone-3.5.5 and Products.PloneFormGen-1.6.0.
- No longer support for Plone-2.5.x.

0.9.6 (2011-02-11)
------------------
- Field security updated to ModifyPortalContent.

0.9.5 (2011-02-06)
------------------
- id added to style verkkomaksut button.

0.9.4 (2011-02-06)
------------------
- Bug, when ORDER_DESCRITION value is driven from text field, is fixed.

0.9.3 (2011-02-06)
------------------
- Bug fix in price_fields method.

0.9.2 (2011-02-06)
------------------
- ORDER_DESCRITION fixed for empty fields.

0.9.1 (2011-02-06)
------------------
- ORDER_NUMBER increase fixed.
- ORDER_DESCRITION fixed.

0.8.0 (2011-02-05)
------------------
- Made Products.GenericSetup aware.

0.7.0 (2011-02-05)
------------------
- verkkomaksut-success template fixed.

0.6.0 (2011-02-05)
------------------
- notify address changed to browser view.

0.5.1 (2011-02-05)
------------------
- Now support thanks message with editor like kupu.
- Result display of multiselectin field is fixed.

0.3.2 (2011-02-04)
------------------
- Added verkkomaksut-canceled page view. Cancelation message is now shown both in Plone-2.5.5 and Plone-3.1.7.

0.2.4 (2011-02-04)
------------------
- ORDER_DESCRIPTION is now fetched from specified field values.
- Custome cancel message field is added.

0.1.1 (2011-02-04)
------------------
- Added mailer function to the adapter.

0.0.9 (2011-01-31)
------------------
- Initial release
- Tested with Products.PloneFormGen-1.2.7 on Plone-2.5.5 and Plone-3.1.7.

Products.PFGVerkkomaksut Installation
-------------------------------------

To install Products.PFGVerkkomaksut into the global Python environment (or a workingenv),
using a traditional Zope 2 instance, you can do this:

* When you're reading this you have probably already run 
  ``easy_install Products.PFGVerkkomaksut``. Find out how to install setuptools
  (and EasyInstall) here:
  http://peak.telecommunity.com/DevCenter/EasyInstall

* If you are using Zope 2.9 (not 2.10), get `pythonproducts`_ and install it 
  via::

    python setup.py install --home /path/to/instance

into your Zope instance.

* Create a file called ``Products.PFGVerkkomaksut-configure.zcml`` in the
  ``/path/to/instance/etc/package-includes`` directory.  The file
  should only contain this::

    <include package="Products.PFGVerkkomaksut" />

.. _pythonproducts: http://plone.org/products/pythonproducts


Alternatively, if you are using zc.buildout and the plone.recipe.zope2instance
recipe to manage your project, you can do this:

* Add ``Products.PFGVerkkomaksut`` to the list of eggs to install, e.g.:

    |    [buildout]
    |    eggs =
    |        Products.PFGVerkkomaksut

* Tell the plone.recipe.zope2instance recipe to install a ZCML slug:

    |    [instance]
    |    recipe = plone.recipe.zope2instance
    |    zcml =
    |        Products.PFGVerkkomaksut

* Re-run buildout, e.g. with:

    |    $ ./bin/buildout

You can skip the ZCML slug if you are going to explicitly include the package
from another package's configure.zcml file.

Because its top level Python namespace package is called ``Products``, this
package can also be installed in Zope 2 as an old style **Zope 2 Product**.

For that, move (or symlink) the ``PFGVerkkomaksut`` folder of this project
(``Products.PFGVerkkomaksut/Products/PFGVerkkomaksut``) into the ``Products`` directory of
the Zope instance it has to be installed for, and restart the server.

You can also skip the ZCML slug if you install this package the **Zope 2
Product** way.

Credits
=========
* Pekka Saari from the Finnish Association for Nature Conservation (Suomen Luonnonsuojeluliitto) who uses this package in their site: http://www.sll.fi
